theorem Topology.P3_implies_interior_closure_eq_interior_closureInteriorClosure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (X:=X) A →
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
  intro hP3
  have h :=
    Topology.P3_implies_closure_eq_closureInteriorClosure (X:=X) (A:=A) hP3
  simpa [h]

set_option maxRecDepth 2000

replace theorem Topology.isOpen_subset_closureInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) : Topology.P1 (X := X) A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  -- Rewriting with `simpa only` avoids the excessive recursion that caused
  -- the previous `simp` failure.
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior A := by
    simpa only [hA.interior_eq] using hx
  exact subset_closure hx_int

replace theorem Topology.Topology.isOpen_subset_closureInterior {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior A := by
    simpa only [hA.interior_eq] using hx
  exact subset_closure hx_int

theorem Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  have h_subset : (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ A := interior_subset
  exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx

theorem Topology.interior_interior_closure_eq_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = interior (closure A) := by
  simpa [interior_interior]
